----------------------------------------------------------------
               Norton Utilities 6.01 READ.ME file
----------------------------------------------------------------

Please read this file for important information on:

* Compatibility with Windows 3.1.
* Changes from prior versions of Norton Utilities.
* New features added since the manuals were printed.
* Questions and Answers.
* Using Norton Utilities with multitasking environments.
* Using Norton Utilities on networks.

If you would like to print this file, change to the directory
where Norton Utilities is installed (e.g. \NU), and at the DOS
prompt type:

      LP READ.ME /H60

You can also use the NDOS command "LIST READ.ME" to display the
file on your screen.

The "Getting Started" chapter of the User Guide states that
this READ.ME file will be available as part of the on-line help
system.  Instead, READ.ME will remain a separate file on disk,
to ensure that the information is the most current available.


Windows 3.1 compatibility
================================================================

Norton Utilities 6.01 is fully compatible with Windows 3.1 in
both Standard and Enhanced mode.

The Windows SETUP program may warn that certain Norton Utilities
TSR's and device drivers are incompatible with Windows 3.1.
This warning is related to prior versions of the Utilities.
All the TSR's and device drivers in this release are compatible
with Windows 3.1.

If you are using the SmartDrive 4.0 disk cache that comes with
Windows 3.1, please refer to the SmartDrive compatibility notes
in the "Questions and Answers" section later in this file.

    
Changes from prior versions of Norton Utilities
================================================================

Information on Norton Cache has been moved from READ.ME to a
separate file called NCACHE.DOC.  Please view or print this file
for the latest information on Norton Cache.

The FILESAVE.EXE program from Norton Utilities 5.0 has been
renamed Erase Protect (EP.EXE).

Some programs from Norton Utilities version 4.5 have been
combined into other programs in version 6.01.  These changes
are noted in the following list:
     
  Version 4.5 Program        Version 6.01 Program
  -----------------------    ---------------------------
  DI - Disk Information      Sysinfo
  DT - Disk Test             NDD
  LD - List Directory        NCD
  NU - Norton Utilities      DiskEdit, UnErase, DiskTool
  QU - Quick UnErase         UnErase
