powerful version is available through the DESCRIBE command
found in NDOS.


New Features
================================================================

Erase Protect
-------------
EP defaults to saving a maximum of Two Megabytes, and protecting
all files except those with TMP or SWP extensions.  This will
improve system performance when using EP and Microsoft Windows.
If you are upgrading from a prior version of Norton Utilities,
you must delete any existing FILESAVE.INI or EP.INI files before
these new defaults will take effect. 

Disk Monitor
------------
DISKMON's protection features are now automatically disabled
when Windows is started, and re-enabled on return to DOS.
This eliminates the need to create a batch file to run Windows,
as was described on page 6-7 of the User's Guide.  Note that
only disk protection is disabled; the disk light will still
be displayed when DOS programs are run under Windows.
    
Disk Tools
----------
Rescue Diskette information may now be saved to and restored
from any drive, not just floppy diskettes.  This allows you to
save the rescue information to a network.  We recommand that
you DO NOT save the information on a local hard disk.  At the
times when you would need to restore the rescue information,
you probably won't be able to access the hard disk!  When saving
or restoring information on a floppy drive, the rescue files
are always located in the root directory.  On any other drive,
Disk Tools will prompt you to enter the directory.

FileFind
--------
The "Drives to Search" dialog box has changed (this dialog is
activated by the Alt-D hotkey, or by pulling down the "Search"
menu and selecting "Search drives").  The drive check boxes
now reflect the "custom" drive selections at all times.  The
check boxes will not be changed when the "Default drive" or
"All drives" radio buttons are selected.

Norton Change Directory
-----------------------
A new command has been added to the "Disk" menu in NCD.  The
"Free Space" command will display the total size, space used,
and available space of the current drive.

Compatibility with Norton PC Anywhere
-------------------------------------
When the Norton Utilities are used remotely via PC Anywhere,
all font redefinitions (including the graphic mouse cursor)
are automatically disabled.  

Compatibility with QEMM 6.0
---------------------------
The Norton Utilities have been tested with QEMM 6.0 and
generally work well.  Please see the QEMM section later in this
READ.ME file for complete information.


Questions and Answers
================================================================

Installation Errors
-------------------
If, for some reason, your are unable to install the Norton
Utilities on your system using the Install program, they
can be installed manually.  The following steps will install
the Norton Utilities:

1) Create a directory on your disk to receive the Norton
Utilities programs, if you don't have one already.  For
example, to install the Norton Utilities in a directory
called NORTON on your hard disk, use the command

MD C:\NORTON

2) Copy the contents of the distribution diskettes to your
Norton Utilities directory.  For example, assuming you
are installing from drive A:, use the command

COPY A:*.* C:\NORTON

for each of the distribution diskettes.

3) There are various files stored in compressed form on
the distribution diskettes.  See the section "Archive
File Extraction Errors" below to extract the compressed
files.  Note that you have already copied the archive
files to the destination directory, and can run the
extractions from there.

4) Now your system must be configured to run the Norton
Utilities whenever you want them.  To have the Norton
Utilities Configuration program do this for you, make
sure you are in the directory with the Norton Utilities,
for example use the commands

C:
CD \NORTON

Then enter the command

NUCONFIG /$INSTALL

and follow the instructions on the screen.  You can
look in the Installation Guide for more details on the
Configuration stage of installation.

5) Finally, if you have made any changes to your system
configuration in step 4, you will need to reboot your
computer for these changes to take effect.

6) You are now ready to use the Norton Utilities!


